            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-046/">LL07-046 "Chika Takami"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="046">
                What happens if I <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %> this card with less than three cards in my Deck?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Even if you have less than three cards in your Deck, you can add one Member without Stars to your Hand and return the rest to the bottom of your Deck.
                However, even if all of them have no Stars, you cannot take another turn, as the requirement for that effect calls for "three cards without Stars" to be shown.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-047/">LL07-047 "Riko Sakurauchi"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="047">
                If I only have one face-up Song card in my Set List, can I flip one face-down Song card face-up?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. The "all your face-up Song cards have the same Attribute" requirement is met in this case, so you can flip one face-down Song card face-up.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-048/">LL07-048 "Kanan Matsuura"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="048_same">
                What does "Member with the same Pieces" mean?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                It means a Member who has the exact same number including Piece attributes as another Member.
                The order of Pieces does not matter, so if you <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %>ed a Member with <%- skillFormat("[SMILE][PURE], you can ⟪ENTER⟫") %> another Member with <%- skillFormat("[PURE][SMILE]") %>.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="048_bday">
                If I <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %> <a href="/card/LL06-008/">LL06-008 "Mari Ohara"</a> with the Birthday Bonus active using this card's Skill, can I <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %> <a href="/card/LL07-051/">LL07-051 "Yoshiko Tsushima"</a> from my Hand?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                Yes. When the Birthday Bonus is active, the bonus Pieces are added to that card, so in this example, you can <%- skillFormat("⟪ENTER⟫") %> <a href="/card/LL07-051/">LL07-051 "Yoshiko Tsushima"</a>.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-049/">LL07-049 "Dia Kurosawa"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="049">
                Can I choose not to draw a card if the designated player decides to let everyone draw cards?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                No. If "Everyone draws a card" is chosen, you and everyone else will always draw a card.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-050/">LL07-050 "You Watanabe"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="050">
                If I 《Enter》 when I have 0 cards in my deck, will the card I put on the bottom of my deck be 《Enter》 as it is?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                yes. Look at the card placed at the bottom of the deck and "appear" one of the members, so the card you put will always "appear".
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-052/">LL07-052 "Hanamaru Kunikida"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#">Is it OK if the condition is the same as "If more than"?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#">[When participating in the live] [When the live is successful] What is the order of skills?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="052">
                Two people are playing a game and both have the same number of cards in their hand. In this situation, what happens if two or more of these cards participate in the same 《Live》?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                The skill of the first player, Hanamaru, draws a card. The second and subsequent "Hanamaru" meet the condition "You have more cards in your hand than any other" at the time of skill, so + [all].
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-053/">LL07-053 "Mari Ohara"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="053">
                Can a member who does not have [All], but has a skill that + [All] such as [When participating in a live], use this card's skill to [Appear]?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                No. Skills such as [When participating in a live] can only be used at the appropriate timing, so when you are in your hand, you are not a member with [All].
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="053">
                [When Appearing] A member who has [Special Practice] with the skill is [appeared], and by becoming awakened, the number of [All] pieces has increased to 3 or more. In this case, can you draw 3 cards?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                yes. This [When entering] skill counts the number of pieces after members appear on the stage. [Special Practice] If you are awakened by a skill, the awakening icon piece will be active when you appear on the stage, so the member will have 3 [All] pieces, including the awakening icon piece. If you have more than that, you meet the conditions.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-055/">LL07-055 "Kinmirai Happy End"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#">What is the status of "Waiting"?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#">Which comes first, opening the song or the [Successful Live] skill?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="055">
                At the time of "live" this song, I achieved the goal live P. If the conditions for the skill are met, can I continue to 《Live》?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                No. Once the target live P is achieved, the winner will be eliminated, so "live" is not possible.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="055">
                What would happen if members other than "CYaRon!" participated in the "live" of this song?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                If "Chika", "You", and "Ruby" are participating, the skill will be effective regardless of the other members.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-056M/">LL07-056M"</a></h5>
            <div class="question" id="056M">
                LL05-053 "Mari Ohara" is playing this song while meeting the skill conditions and performing live, with members with [Smile], members with [Pure], and members with [Cool]. "I participated in. In this case, will the skill be +【All】?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                No. The skill of this song changes all the [Smile], [Pure], and [Cool] pieces of the participating members to [All] before the [When participating in a live] skill. Therefore, in this case, +[all] is not performed.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="056M">
                The member who participated in the "live" was given a + [smile] by the skill "When participating in the live" while the song was being played live with the skill conditions met. Does this piece also become [All] by skill?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                yes. A piece becomes [all] when it is added.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="056M">
                What will happen if members other than "AZALEA" participate in the "live" of this song?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                As long as "Kanan", "Dia" and "Hanamaru" are participating, the skill will be effective regardless of the other members.
            </div>

            <h5><a href="/card/LL07-057/">LL07-057 "Kowareyasuki"</a></h5>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#">[When participating in the live] [When the live is successful] What is the order of skills?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="seealso">
                See also: <a href="/faq/general#">Which comes first, opening the song or the [Successful Live] skill?</a>
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="057">
                What exactly do you mean when you say "each person may appear"?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                It means that "up to one "Riko", one "Yoshiko", and one "Mari" may appear". It is possible to 《Appear》 three people one by one, or to 《Appear》 one by one “Riko” and “Yoshiko”.
            </div>
            <div class="question" id="057">
                What will happen if members other than "Guilty Kiss" participate in the "live" of this song?
            </div>
            <div class="answer">
                If "Riko", "Yoshiko", and "Mari" are participating, the skill will be effective regardless of the other members.
            </div>

